  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2009-05-07",
    "date": "2009-06-05T19:41:52Z",
    "text": "Excessive Pay Shareholder Approval Act - Amends the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 to prohibit the compensation for an employee of an issuer of securities in any single taxable year from exceeding 100 times the average compensation for services performed by all the issuer's employees during such taxable year.\n\nAllows higher compensation only if at least 60% of the shareholders have voted to approve it (through a proxy or consent or authorization for an annual or other meeting of the shareholders, occurring within the preceding 18 months)."
  },
